OL,4,CClimate change: Courts set for rise in
OL,5,Ccompensation cases
OL,6, There's likely to be a significant
OL,7, increase in the number of lawsuits
OL,8, brought against fossil fuel companies
OL,9, in the coming years, say researchers.
OL,11,FTheir new study finds that to date,
OL,12,Flawyers have failed to use the most
OL,13,Fup-to-date scientific evidence on the
OL,14,Fcause of rising temperatures.
OL,16,FAs a result, there have been few
OL,17,Fsuccessful claims for compensation.
OL,19,FThat could change, say the authors, as
OL,20,Fevidence linking specific weather
OL,21,Fevents to carbon emissions increases.
